snippet.textDisplay:
The virus-ravaged city of Wuhan has been completely sealed off from the outside world for more than a month. All resources, from food to medical supplies, have become scarce there. Many people have lost their lives to the coronavirus, with some dropping dead as they walked the street.

At this critical time, many Falun Dafa practitioners are making phone calls to China to offer hope and blessings.

Below are two examples of people feeling better after talking to practitioners on the phone and quitting the Chinese Communist Party (CCP).

Falun Gong practitioner Ms. Chen called a man in Wuhan and asked how he was.

“Umm,” the man responded.

Ms. Chen told him that the coronavirus epidemic was a man-made disaster and that, in ancient times, people would see such an epidemic as a warning from heaven of moral decline and corruption. Noting that the CCP has done so many bad things in China, she urged the man to quit the Party and its affiliated organizations so that he would be blessed by heaven.

The man agreed.

Ms. Chen noticed that the man kept coughing and was having difficulty talking and breathing. When she asked him if he was alright, the man responded, “I feel like I’m dying.”

Ms. Chen then said, “How about you recite two phrases after me? I know it has helped many people. Please say, ‘Falun Dafa is good; Truthfulness-Compassion-Forbearance is good.’”

The man repeated the phrases after her for more than ten minutes. When he was out of breath, Ms. Chen kept saying it for him.

Suddenly, he coughed deeply and then he felt his airways were clear. He talked to Ms. Chen for another 40 minutes and thanked her for helping him.

Ms. Chen next called a woman in her 70s, who also agreed to quit the CCP’s affiliated organizations after talking to her.

As they were talking, the woman suddenly said, “Now I can breathe so much easier. Thank you!”

After the woman’s daughter-in-law witnessed what happened to her mother, she also agreed to quit the CCP.
